<hr />
<p>Hey Bob,</p>
<p>We tested those new toys your eggheads dreamed up. The invisibility and shock gear preformed as expected. But the real star was the light show you cooked up. When you told me to get the agents to scribble in the dirt after they had finished up testing the other stuff, I thought you had lost it! But the results speak for themselves. I got the video and pictures you wanted, its in the mail. So are all the full observations, all pretty and scientific like you asked. Too many words to say “earth shattering kaboom” if you ask me.</p>
<p>Oh, and I lost a fair few operatives in this little shindig. No one important but I don’t have an unlimited supply of people crazy enough to test your gadgets but sensible enough to keep their traps shut. Not to mention the cover story for what your space laser did. What I’m saying is, you owe me one.</p>
<p>I’ll see you next time I’m in DC. Shouldn’t be more than a couple months.</p>
<p>Cheers,<br />
Gerald Bostock<br />
CIA-PENTAGRAM Liaison Officer</p>
